Open Babyphone (fork of Child Monitor)
======================================

June 2026: 1.1.0-alpha.3

  * App icon redesigned to paired-phones brand mark (#135)
  * All runtime screens redesigned with Open Design brand palette and components (#138, #140)
  * Website landing page updated with brand mark (#136)
  * Monochrome themed launcher icon added (#109)
  * Microphone sensitivity control on child device: Normal, High, Very high (#127)
  * One-time trusted child pairing flow: parents remember known children and reconnect without re-scanning (#117)
  * Add parent devices while child monitoring is active (#116)
  * Connection-lost alert hardened: pairing code removed from deep links (#132)
  * Active parent pairing dialog polished (#133)
  * Wi-Fi Direct experimental connection mode (#77)
  * QR code scanner in parent mode for child pairing
  * Parent-side audio focus request with AudioFocusRequest and AudioTrack.Builder
  * ListenService playback thread InterruptedException handling (#102)
  * Public docs rewritten with friendlier, product-oriented tone (#101)
  * Explicit Android data extraction rules (#108)
  * Real-device reliability test matrix expanded to 40 scenarios
  * Power management and OEM battery optimization guidance documented
  * Version bumped to 1.1.0-alpha.3 (versionCode 18)

June 2026: Initial fork release (1.1.0-alpha)

  * Project renamed to Open Babyphone
  * Migrated the Android application ID to `org.openbabyphone` before public release
  * Migrated the internal Android namespace and Kotlin source package to `org.openbabyphone`
  * Added optional persistent pairing code for authentication
  * Modernized CI with GitHub Actions (JDK 21, Android SDK 34)
  * English-only app (removed translations)
  * Added unit tests for codec, framing, jitter buffer, crypto, and client management
  * Added optional ChaCha20-Poly1305 stream encryption when a pairing code is configured
  * Replaced plaintext pairing code transmission with challenge-response authentication
  * Added per-session random nonces to prevent AEAD nonce reuse across sessions
  * Froze pairing code during active monitoring sessions to prevent key mismatches
  * Focus on local-network baby monitoring for home use
  * Trusted VPN use is treated as an advanced manual setup note, not the normal setup flow

Child Monitor (original project)
================================

Sun Jan 3, 2016: Release 0.2

  * Improve and simplify audio playback to reduce dropped
    audio samples

  * A parent device may pair with a child device by entering
    the child's IP address and port.

  * Japanese translation


Mon Dec 28, 2015: Release 0.1

 * Initial release